reviews.headline: Shade was wrong in the tube
reviews.comments: I have gone to three separate ulta locations and Each time the color inside is too orange so then I had the Ulta employee mail one to my house and it was still too orange so It must be a manufacturing error, but it's so frustrating that the concealer I've been using for so long is the wrong color and anybody I have to talk to about it at the various ulta stores I've been to Do not care.

reviews.headline: The best!
reviews.comments: I own and have tried so very many concealers and this is the absolute best as far as not getting into lines or wearing off. I can't recommend it enough!

reviews.headline: Disappointed it's not on a stick form
reviews.comments: I do not wear makeup much so when I was recently time to replenish a couple of things, I was looking forward to getting exactly the same product. When I got home to try on the concealer, I was disappointed that it wasn't in stick form anymore. It had a wand for application.  That's my only complaint. I wish it was in stick form again for application.

reviews.headline: I keep buying this product over and over.
reviews.comments: So far it's working

reviews.headline: Best concealer for dry skin
reviews.comments: I have yet to find a better concealer than this for dry thinning skin under the eyes. I am 45 and have been using this for the past few years. I have eczema and generally dryer skin, plus my skin is thinning a bit more so it gets that crepe feel. This goes on smooth, you can use your finger easily, or a small brush, I wouldn't use the foam things. You can layer a little if you need more coverage in certain areas. It blends and does not cake, if it does, you can smooth it out with your finger again. Love it so much!

reviews.comments:

reviews.comments: I tried blending this out with a brush and a sponge but it was so patchy and it dried to fast i had to blend it the second it was on. Maybe it was js me but its a no for me ive tried better.

reviews.headline: Definitely not Cakeless!
reviews.comments: Concealers unfortunately are a necessity! I've tried dozens over the years and I'm still searching. I had hoped Benefit's Cakeless Concealer would be the answer, however the worst quality of it was that it caked excessively. I really tried, in fact I used it on a clean moisturized face four times. I only wanted to cover a little discoloration and give a fresher appearance under my eyes. Fortunately, I don't have bags under my eyes to contend with. I quickly learned that less is better with this product. However in my attempt to blend and/or build the concealer the result was very "cakey". I think Benefit needs to change the name and claim of this concealer! Too bad too, because I love their other products and I had such high hopes.

faceoff_positive.comments:
First Impressions -

Anyway, overall I would say I really like this concealer. I try to avoid things like this because of my sensitive/oily skin type, but by far this has been living up to my expectations.

First of all, it came in a very pretty and light-colored packaging and the item itself had a very cute design. It has the design of a medium-sized pencil and the main frame is glass with black writing on the front. Its very simple, but cute.

 Inspecting & Applying - 

Now, when opened, it doesn't have a strong nor offending smell. Its very faint, which is a go to when you are not looking for one laced with chemicals.

 As for the concealer itself, it has a slight thicker texture than other concealers I have used. Yet, with the cushion tip, it made it quite easy to apply it despite this. It smoothed out very easily and blended very evenly. 

Though, at first do to its color, I mostly used it around my eyes as a test. But, it passed very efficiently at hiding my dark circles and unevenness around my eyes. So, only after then, I used it as a full coverage concealer. In which, it did even better. It hid my dark spots and my blemishes quite effectively with an overall smooth finish. So, I absolutely love the option of both coverage options.

This product's NO.10, kinda reminds me of M¬∑A¬∑C Pro Longwear Concealer NC45, but comparably better in feel & quality.

It overall looked amazing. It also felt good on my skin and blended well with other makeup. I didn't have any allergic reactions when using and my oily skin didn't disrupt the concealer too much. It felt very lightweight on my skin and it did live up to its claims of not caking. It stayed on evenly and lasted me quite long throughout the day. 

I have yet to try out its waterproof compatiblities, but it lives up well to its others. So, by far, I haven't had any issues, but this is a wonderful concealer I was very excited to try and I am very glad I did. 
I received this product complimentary for test and review.

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received this product for free from Benefit (through an app which I am not able to log into on my cell phone or tablet so I am writing it here on my PC) as part of a contest and I couldn't wait to test it out and wear it; however I found that some of the claims such as the waterproof were not so accurate. 
I was easily able to wash the concealer off without any soap and while the application wasn't cakey to begin with the longer I wore it the heavier my face began to feel and the feeling that my skin wasn't getting any air was very noticeable. 
I also found that this was not as full coverage as some other brands that I have used in the past. The coverage when blended out looked streaky / splotchy on my face against the foundations I tried it with. I am pretty sure it pulled up the drug store foundation when I tested it out.
The cushion tip seemed to hold onto the product well, but when swiped barely anything came off the applicator onto my skin.
Finally the shade range seems a little limited with only 12 shades to choose from, I am a little bummed out there.
The packaging is very cute as the unicarton is definately some aesthetically pleasing colors. I found the pencil eraser tip to be very adorable on the product itself and it was very light weight all around. It's small and easily tossed into a makeup bag or kit and taken when you're on the go.

For the price I would say it's a fair deal and I know not all shades have the same formula as different undertones and shades require different mixes of ingredients. But I am disappointed in the product after having waited so eagerly to test it out and wear it for the first time. 
Again I did receive this product for free in a contest from Benefit through an app.
